  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study describes the difference of analgesic effect of levobupivacaine 0.5% administered
      through an interscalene nerve block with or without a stellate ganglion block. The length of
      the analgesic effect is our primary outcome parameter. Half of the recruited patients will
      receive a stellate ganglion block and half of the patients won't.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
